en: Nonviolent communication evolved from concepts used in person-centered therapy, and was developed by clinical psychologist Marshall Rosenberg beginning in the 1960s and 1970s.
fr: La communication non violente a évolué à partir de concepts utilisés dans la thérapie centrée sur la personne, et a été développée par le psychologue clinicien Marshall Rosenberg dans les années 1960 et 1970.

en: Nonviolent communication holds that most conflicts between individuals or groups arise from miscommunication about their human needs.
fr: La communication non violente soutient que la plupart des conflits entre individus ou groupes proviennent d'une mauvaise communication sur leurs besoins humains.

en: Nonviolent communication is a tool for transforming potential conflicts into peaceful dialogues.
fr: La communication non violente est un outil pour transformer les conflits potentiels en dialogues paisibles.

en: Nonviolent communication is an approach to communication based on principles of nonviolence.
fr: La communication non violente est une approche de la communication basée sur les principes de la non-violence.

en: Nonviolent communication is used both as a clinical psychotherapy modality and as a self-help technique, particularly with regards to seeking harmony in relationships and at workplaces.
fr: La communication non violente est utilisée à la fois comme une modalité de psychothérapie clinique et comme une technique d'auto-assistance, notamment en ce qui concerne la recherche de l'harmonie dans les relations et sur le lieu de travail.

en: NVC distinguishes real feelings from words describing thoughts, judgments, and interpretations.

en: NVC focuses on effective strategies for meeting fundamental needs for all parties in a conversation.

en: NVC has been applied in organizational and business settings, in parenting, in education, in mediation, in psychotherapy, in healthcare, in addressing eating issues, in justice, and as a basis for a children's book, among other contexts.
